# Project Structure and Dependencies

## Core Technologies
- Next.js 15
- React 19
- TypeScript
- Supabase for authentication and database
- Tailwind CSS for styling

## Key Dependencies
- `@supabase/ssr` - Server-side Supabase integration
- `zod` - Schema validation
- `lucide-react` - Icon library
- `next/headers` - Cookie handling
- `next/cache` - Cache management

## Project Organization
```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js app directory
│   ├── login/             # Authentication pages
│   ├── signup/            # Signup flow
│   └── dashboard/         # Protected dashboard area
├── components/            # React components
├── utils/                 # Utility functions
│   └── supabase/         # Supabase client setup
└── lib/                   # Shared libraries
```

## Key Architectural Decisions
1. Server Components by default
2. Client Components only when needed (e.g., forms with optimistic updates)
3. Server Actions for data mutations
4. Selective cache invalidation
5. Type-safe database operations with Supabase
